        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">What Is Fishing?</h2>

      <p class="text-gray-300">Fishing means playing a low-scoring move (1-2 tiles) specifically to keep 5-6 tiles that form a strong bingo stem. You sacrifice immediate points gambling that your next draw completes a 7-letter word.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 The Math</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">If your best play scores 28 and your fishing play scores 12, you sacrifice 16 points. If you bingo next turn for 75+ points (average bingo value), the gamble pays <span class="text-white font-medium">+59 net points</span> when it works. Even at 30% success, the expected value often favours fishing.</p>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">When to Fish</h2>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✓ Fish When</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Your leave contains a top-20 bingo stem • The board has open 7+ tile lanes • The bag has 20+ tiles remaining • The point gap between plays is less than 20 • You're not critically behind (50+ points down)</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-red-500/30 bg-red-950/10">
          <p class="text-red-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✗ Don't Fish When</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">The board is closed (no bingo lanes) • The bag has fewer than 10 tiles • You'd sacrifice 25+ points • Your leave isn't a recognised stem • You're in the endgame</p>
        </div>
      </div>

